name Fried Mozzarella with Mango Salad
serves 6
tags main, vegetarian, italian, salad

# Preparation

- 60 g shallots
- 1 clove garlic
- 4 spring onions
- 50 g capers
- 2 tbsp white wine vinegar
- 6 tbsp olive oil
- "orange juice"
- "ginger"
- "peanuts (roasted, unsalted)"
- salt
- pepper
- sugar
Finely dice the shallots, chop the garlic and slice the spring onions into thin rings.
Purée the ginger and peanuts. Mix everything together and season with salt, pepper and sugar.

- 400 g vine tomatoes
Wash the tomatoes, cut out the stems and slice thinly. Arrange in a shallow dish and
drizzle with ⅓ of the vinaigrette.
-> marinated tomatoes

- 2 mangoes
@nodep
Peel the mangoes and slice the flesh thinly from the stone.
-> mango

- 375 g mozzarella
- 8 slices sandwich bread
@nodep
Remove the crusts from the bread. Slice the mozzarella thinly, season lightly with salt
and arrange on 4 slices of bread. Cover with the remaining 4 slices and press together
gently. Cut diagonally in half.

- 4 eggs
- breadcrumbs
Lightly beat the eggs. Dip the sandwiches first in the egg, then in the breadcrumbs,
making sure the cut edges are thoroughly coated.
-> breaded sandwiches

- 12 "large basil leaves"
= mango
= marinated tomatoes
Mix the mango and basil with the tomatoes and remaining vinaigrette, season lightly with
salt and pepper and divide between plates.

= breaded sandwiches
Heat oil in a pan and fry the sandwiches in 2 batches until golden. Drain briefly on
kitchen paper and serve immediately alongside the salad.
